bug.short_desc: [abrt] ibus: ibus_emojier_run(): ibus killed by SIGABRT
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: - start "ibus emoji" - above the categories I see a button labelled "English" - I click that button - a list of languages appears - I click on any language (In this case the first one, "Afrikaans", but any language will do -> core dump
Version-Release number of selected component: ibus-1.5.15-1.fc25
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.8.0 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: ibus emoji crash_function: ibus_emojier_run executable: /usr/bin/ibus global_pid: 7761 kernel: 4.9.13-200.fc25.x86_64 pkg_vendor: (none) runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1000
Truncated backtrace: Thread no. 1 (4 frames) #4 ibus_emojier_run at emojier.c:3471 #5 run_dialog at main.c:1642 #6 ___lambda4_ at main.c:1720 #7 ____lambda4__ibus_emojier_loaded_emoji_dict at main.c:1727

Created attachment 1261238 Patch for tools/main.vala
Thank you for filing the bug. I can reproduce your problem now if the process is slow.
